Police in Lagos have arrested two Chinese nationals for allegedly abusing their roommate sexually through anus. The suspects who are identified as Yang Liang Ming, 41 and Mr. Wang Gui-Moi, 45 were arrested following a complaint to Police in Area F Command by one of the roommate, Jun Lan – Yin  who alleged that they are forcefully making love with him through the anus. Police detectives immediately swung into action led by Assistant Commissioner of Police, ACP,Olasóji Akinbayo and arrested the two suspects and detained them for interrogation. Our correspondent however gathered that both suspects deny the allegations. The police said preliminary investigation revealed that there was sexual assault by the two suspects. This was further corroborated by medical reports from Mirabel Medical Centre, at the Lagos State Teaching Hospital (LASUTH), which confirms that Mr Jun Lan-Yin was sexually assaulted by his colleagues-cum-housemate. Our Correspondent also gathered that both the suspects and complainant are staff of Life Mate Furniture and are illegal immigrants whose visas have expired. Investigations further revealed that the suspects have a record of being gay at their former place of work and the company is ready to testify against them if necessary. 